### Most critical gap
**`red-cell-c2-425c`** — `operator.rs` has no test verifying that a message with an unknown `EventCode` (e.g., `0xFF`) or a valid event code but unknown SubEvent returns a serde error. The catch-all arm at line 1025 is the last line of defence against malformed operator messages; without a test, a refactoring could silently swallow the error or panic.

### Overall quality
The codebase has strong test discipline. `tls.rs`, `agent_liveness.rs`, and `agents.rs` are exemplary. The main gap is in `api.rs` — three REST endpoints (`GET /listeners/{name}`, `GET /webhooks`, and the `create_listener` error paths) have no direct test coverage despite being part of the documented public API surface.
